  <h2>The Convenience of an On-Site Pharmacy</h2>
  <p>
    When your pet leaves our hospital, they may need to start a medication the same day. Our in-house pharmacy means you can pick up everything you need before you go home — heartworm prevention, antibiotics, pain medication, flea and tick control, and more.
  </p>
  <p>
    We stock a wide range of veterinary-grade medications and can often fill prescriptions immediately after your pet's exam.
  </p>

  <h2>Why In-House Matters</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Authentic, veterinary-grade medications</strong> — sourced directly from licensed veterinary pharmaceutical manufacturers</li>
    <li><strong>No gray market risk</strong> — unlike some online retailers, we guarantee the authenticity and proper storage of every product we dispense</li>
    <li><strong>Immediate start</strong> — your pet can begin treatment the same day, which matters most for infections, pain, and post-surgical care</li>
    <li><strong>Expert guidance</strong> — our team reviews dosing, side effects, and administration instructions before you leave</li>
    <li><strong>Chronic condition support</strong> — ongoing medications for conditions like thyroid disease, diabetes, arthritis, or allergies can be managed and refilled through us</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Post-Surgery and Acute Care</h2>
  <p>
    After a surgical procedure, your pet will typically need pain management medication, antibiotics, or both. Having these ready before discharge means less stress for you and a smoother recovery for your pet.
  </p>

  <h2>Online Pharmacy</h2>
  <p>
    For routine maintenance medications or refills, we also offer access to our trusted online pharmacy partner. You can order from home and have medications shipped directly to your door.
  </p>
